DeadlineLovebirds\" /><ref name=\"DeadlineBeastie\" />\n\n=== Cancelled ===\n<!-- Please insert in alphabetical order! Thanks! -->\n*''[[Artemis Fowl (film)|Artemis Fowl]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and to be released on [[Disney+]] on June 12, 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1250952145550991360|title=#ArtemisFowl is streaming exclusively June 12 on #DisneyPlus.|user=disneyplus|date=April 16, 2020|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"HollywoodNewDisney\" />\n*''[[Beastie Boys Story]]'' \u2013 [[IMAX]] release on April 3, 2020 cancelled and to be released on [[Apple TV+]] on April 24.<ref name=\"DeadlineBeastie\" />\n*''[[Blue Story]]'' \u2013 Limited theatrical release in the U.S. cancelled and to be released on [[Video on Demand|VOD]] on May 5, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/blue-story/id1501799635|website=[[iTunes]]|title=Blue Story|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[Endings, Beginnings]]'' \u2013 Released on [[Video on Demand|VOD]] on April 17, 2020, with a [[HBO]] release on a yet-to-be determined date.\n*''[[Enter the Fat Dragon (2020 film)|Enter the Fat Dragon]]'' \u2013 Premiered online.{{efn|Except in the Philippines, where the film had already gone to theaters on January 29, 2020, before the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|COVID-19 arrival in the country]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RealityEntPH/status/1222323823380353025|title=The fat dragon is finally here! You can now watch Enter The Fat Dragon in cinemas near you. #EnterTheFatDragon #ThisIsREALITY|author=Reality Entertainment|date=January 28, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130060946/https://twitter.com/RealityEntPH/status/1222323823380353025|archive-date=January 30, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n*''[[Lost in Russia]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and released on [[TikTok]], [[Toutiao]], Xigua on January 25, 2020 for free.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Patrick Frater |title=China\u2019s \u2018Lost in Russia\u2019 Switches to Unprecedented Online Release in Response to Coronavirus Outbreak |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/asia/coronavirus-china-lost-in-russia-online-release-1203478139/ |accessdate=25 January 2020 |work=variety |date=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[The Lovebirds (2020 film)|The Lovebirds]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and to be released on [[Netflix]] on May 22, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y-rRtM7sC5A|website=YouTube|date=April 20, 2020|title=The Lovebirds {{!}} Issa Rae & Kumail Nanjiani {{!}} Official Trailer {{!}} Netflix}}</ref><ref name=\"DeadlineLovebirds\" />\n*''[[My Spy]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release in the U.S. cancelled and to be released on [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime Video]] on a yet to-be determined date.<ref>{{cite web|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/my-spy-acquired-by-amazon-studios-stx-dave-bautista-1202903723/|title=\u2018My Spy\u2019: STX Dave Bautista Action Comedy Acquired By Amazon Studios For Streaming|date=April 8, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n*''[[Scoob!]]'' - Theatrical release cancelled and to be released on VOD on May 15, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/scoob-home-release-skip-movie-theaters-coronavirus-1202914059/|title=\u2018Scoob!\u2019 To Skip Theaters & Head Into Homes; How Director Tony Cervone Got Animated Pic Across The Finish Line In COVID-19 Climate|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=April 21, 2020|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n* ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]'' \u2013 This film's [[Fathom Events]] release on March 23, 2020 was cancelled after theaters across the country closed as a precautionary measure.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harrigan |first1=Will |title=Fathom Events Cancels and Postpones Movies Due To Coronavirus |url=https://cosmicbook.news/fathom-events-cancel-postpones-coronavirus |website=Cosmic Book News |accessd