\u2013 This film's [[Fathom Events]] release on March 23, 2020 was cancelled after theaters across the country closed as a precautionary measure.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harrigan |first1=Will |title=Fathom Events Cancels and Postpones Movies Due To Coronavirus |url=https://cosmicbook.news/fathom-events-cancel-postpones-coronavirus |website=Cosmic Book News |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> The episode of ''[[Steven Universe Future]]'' that was supposed to play after this screening, \"Homeworld Bound\", showed up on [[Cartoon Network]]'s website the day the event was to take place.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murphy |first1=Jackson |title=Rebecca Sugar Discusses the Final \u201cSteven Universe Future\u201d |url=http://www.animationscoop.com/rebecca-sugar-discusses-the-final-steven-universe-future/ |website=Animation Scoop |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[Time to Hunt (film)|Time to Hunt]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled. Originally to have been released on Netflix on April 10, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|first=Yeon-soo|last=Kwak|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/689_286633.html|title='Time to Hunt' skips theaters and goes straight to Netflix|date=March 23, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324084152/https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/689_286633.html|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> the streaming service's debut of the film was itself postponed two days earlier to comply with a ruling in the Seoul Central District Court regarding distribution contracts.<ref>{{cite web|first=Gyu-lee|last=Lee|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/689_287636.html|title=Netflix halts 'Time to Hunt' release, promotion after injunction|date=April 9, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> The film was released on April 23, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|first=Ye-rang|last=Kim|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/202004201829H|title='\uc0ac\